"This work presents a mobile location management technique based on the clustering. This technique can be implemented on next generation mobile networks by exp loiting the data available on the users (age, function, address, workplace… etc), existing infrastructure (roads, location of base stations… etc) and the users' displacements history The simu lations are carried out using a realistic model of movements. The results show that our strategy requires a min imu m number of location messages compared to the static and dynamic location management techniques."
